uide and force. Including profiles of the hunters and their songs and accompanied (online) by original audio tracks of more than fifty Cree hunting songs, Essential Song makes an important contribution to ethnomusicology, social history, and Aboriginal studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCree IndianszManitobaxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aCree IndianszQuébec (Province)zNord-du-QuébecxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aHunting songszCanada, Northern. 0aIndians of North AmericazCanadavMusic. 0aSongs, Cree. 4aIndigenous Studies. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Ethnomusicology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458144340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554581443/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles